---

Design Principles Applied

âœ” Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)

This class holds constants only; it does not contain logic or methods.

âœ” Maintainability & Scalability

Developers can update stats, paths, or balance values in one place.

âœ” Readability

Clear naming conventions help avoid confusion or misconfiguration.

âœ” Avoiding Magic Numbers

All numeric values are represented symbolically for clarity.


---

Benefits

Centralized control over stats and resource paths

Easy balancing and tweaking without modifying multiple classes

Reduces chances of inconsistencies or typos

Clean, structured organization of asset references



---

Future Enhancements

Separate constants into multiple classes (AudioConstants, RoosterStats, UIPaths) for improved modularity

Add elemental type strengths/weaknesses for advanced combat mechanics

Create JSON or XML configuration to allow dynamic editing without recompiling

Support multiple skins and additional rooster variants



